1) Global Varibale : Variable which are declared outside of the function and has access in whole program. "global" keyword is used inside the function to make the variable gloabl.
2) local Variable : Variable which are declared inside the function and has scope only in that function.

#Example of Global and Local variable

var = "Hello"                  #Global Variable
def get_value():
    global b                   # keyword global is used to make the variable global inside the fucntion
    b = 25                     # local Variable
    print(b)

get_value()
